Lord Bilimoria, the president of the Confederation of British Industry, argued it threatened to "stifle what is already a fragile recovery". The founder of Cobra Beer said the heavy tax burden was wrong "when businesses have suffered so much".  But Lord Bilimoria also flagged his opposition to Labour calls for a windfall tax on oil and gas firms - which have benefited from soaring global prices - in order to help fund a cut in consumers' energy bills. The independent crossbencher said in Parliament it would put at risk investment critical to the UK reaching its "net zero" climate goal. 